@undefined as mentioned in the onboarding form (https://forms.ns.com/onboarding), you can only submit the Arrival Cards for both Singapore and Malaysia 3 days before your planned date of entry. So if you're arriving on Sept 23, you can fill the Arrival Cards after Sept 20. 

For Singapore Arrival Card, most people will fall into the foreign visitor category. LTVP (long term visitor pass) is has very specific requirements that you can check here: https://www.ica.gov.sg/reside/LTVP. 

For Malaysia DAC, you can fill in your best guess if you aren't certain of some details (e.g. date of departure). However, you should ensure that the details are valid based on your visa requirements. E.g. as a US citizen, you get 90 days visa-free, so your date of departure should be within 90 days of the date of entry. We'll share bus info closer to the date. And yes, you can go with Hotel, Johor, Gelang Patah, and 81550 for the other details.
